Agenda

	* What is an exception ?

		when we execute the program due to some problems program execution stop is called exception.
		when a event triggered and stops the program execution is called exception.

		EXCEPTION is an event that occurs during the execution of a program that distrups the normal flow
		of instructions.

	* What is exception handling ?
	* Why do we need exception handling ?
	* Different types of exceptions ?
		They are two types of exception
		* Checked Exception ( compile-time exception)
		* Unchecked Exception ( runtime exception )

